details: Little Stars Learning is a small group in-home child care located in the greater Kansas City area. Many of my parent clients are former gifted and advanced students, who see the same potential and learning needs in their children.  I strongly believe that infants need to be held and played with as much as possible until 6 months. As of 4 months, we get them down for a lot of tummy time, and by 6 months they are spending more time on individual discovery. Infants have a curriculum based upon crossing-the-midline brain training, core strengthening, language acquisition, and sensory stimulation. My philosophy is Reggio inspired, child-led, teacher-facilitated interactive learning through play and movement, with a lot of free time to create, explore and play with loose parts. My graduates are at the top of their respective classes, with most in gifted programs. I believe in a whole-body, 5 senses learning approach with stepped concept introduction. Children are not pushed, nor are they restrained in their learning. I attempt to keep within the very narrow window of optimum learning where they are challenged and interested, never frustrated nor bored. Since the children direct most of the learning direction, they have buy-in and ownership, leading to a great deal of emergent curriculum and topicality. Worksheets are not actively utilized unless a child achieves studies at around a second grade level, when they become developmentally appropriate. Many of my graduates have been assessed for kindergarten at a 2nd and 3rd grade level. A few worksheet are also introduced in the last few months prior to leaving for kindergarten for experience. Many Montessori-type activities are incorporated into our school. However, unlike in a traditional Montessori program where tasks are "taught" and "practiced," here, they are simply part of our day. For instance, a classic Montessori activity is to have a tray of small items to sweep into a small dust pan. Here, the children actually do sweep. They also mop, use a vacuum, and clean up all of their own messes to the best of their ability. Practice is done through performance. I strongly follow Maria Montessori's directive: Never do for a child what he can do for himself! I believe that children are supremely competent. I do not expect them to perform above their developmental capability, but also do not expect them to perform BELOW it, either. As in the Waldorf and Nature School philosophies, we are very keen on the integration of nature through pets, insect studies, our organic garden, sensory input from the flowers and herbs, and immersion in a variety of biomes within our outdoor space. We are very farm-to-table in our learning and eating. ​We also strive for a preponderance of natural elements within our school environment. This is a collaborative school with students, parents, teacher and children's extended family all having a role in shaping the environment and direction of their learning path. The school environment, rules, and expectations are intended to be extended into the home environment. This is not a school for parents who want to plop their children in front of a television at the end of the day, or let them run rampant.

The program is prepared in advance by the program supervisor and the camp staff. A schedule of specialized activities will be made available each week. This program includes breakfast, lunch and daily field trips.

details: My name is Amy McMonagle and I am the owner and primary provider for BuggaBee and Me. ​I have had a passion for working with children from a very young age. Whether baby hogging the newest addition to the family or playing teacher with the neighborhood friends, I knew I wanted to work with kids when I grew up.  In 2005 I met the love of my life, Keith McMonagle, who was and still is serving in the Air Force. We moved to Derby in 2011, from Northern California (Keith came from his 3 year tour in Japan) and have grown to love it here. On September 28th 2015, we welcomed our daughter Waverlee Craine McMonagle into our lives and into the Buggabee and Me family. I am so happy to be a mother and very grateful to be able to be home with her and do a job that I love!

Hi my name is Kim Meitler and I am starting up small licensed daycare from my home! I am certified in CPR/FIRST AID for adult/infant/child along with classes in basic child development and safe sleep practices. I am originally from Wichita but graduated from Rose Hill Highschool in 1999.  After that I went to Cowley County College for my Associates of science and then moved on to Fort Hays State University where I earned my bachelors in nursing in 2006!!!! From then on I worked on the surgical floor and the pacu area at Hays Med Center.  In 2009 I met my spouse Nick Green who is from Norton, KS and in November 2012 we had our beautiful daughter Adilya!!! In 2013 Nick landed a job with pepsi in Wichita and so we packed up and moved to Derby KS! Our home is located near 63rd and Buckner Rd.  Luckily I landed a job close to home and worked at the Derby Ambulatory Surgery Center for just short of two years!!!! After expecting our 2nd child in Feburary 2015 I decided I wanted to stay at home with my babies and start up a small daycare!!!  We our also the parents of 2 small schnauzers who remain put away during daycare hours!!! My daycare is ran on the main floor with a toy room, bathroom, large living room area, dining room and kitchen. Our basement is finished and will be used for storms if needed!!! We also have a fenced in backyard as well!!! If the weather permits we will spend a large amount of time spent outside so the children and run and play and use their imaginations!!! Our backyard has a concrete area for the children to ride on cars or play with chalk and we also have a covered porch for some shaded space. However while inside we will have free play time, story time, arts and crafts, singing and dance time, and loads of fun!!!!!! I do plan on offering a curriculum to the older children once I get more established and settled!!!! I absolutely love small children and their creative minds and will treat your children like my children!!!

details: With a 14 year history in childcare, and 4 young children of their own, owners Misti and Darrick Stephen started the first Scribbles and Giggles location in October of 2010. This small family owned company has grown at this rate of speed because of the heart and dedication that goes into every decision made. Scribbles and Giggles Children’s Academy is known in the community as the fastest growing childcare center in Wichita. With their unparalleled vision for what childcare should be, they have created a huge gap between them and other childcare centers in the area. They offer a completely different childcare experience in which families are more part of an extended family than just a number in a big corporation. Putting families first and ensuring that they hire only staff that are in line with their vision has rocketed the company to success. Scribbles and Giggles Children’s Academy serves children ages 2 weeks to 12 years of age. They have 5 permanent locations under Scribbles and Giggles, Inc. which are family owned and managed. In addition to full day childcare, they offer drop in care, part time care and a latchkey program for school age kids. They offer transportation to all Goddard elementary schools, St. Peter Catholic School, Asbury Preschool, St. Francis Catholic School, Derby schools and Kensler Elementary. Scribbles and Giggles Children’s Academy accepts SRS assistance, St. Francis foster payment, KVC and Youthville sponsored children. We are also a member of the Child and Adult Care Food Program. We hope you will give us the opportunity to prove ourselves to you and more importantly to your children. We understand that sometimes change can be difficult, but we guarantee we will give 100% and will operate these centers in a way that will allow you to feel comfortable leaving your children with us. We know that they are your most prized possession! We promise to provide an environment in which they learn self-confidence and were they will feel loved!

As rewarding as parenting is, it can be a tough job at times. However, you don’t have to bear the burden by yourself. In a time when finding capable and concerned supervision for your young children can be challenging, you can count on Smart Start Daycare in Wichita, Kansas. We are a day care center for kids aged six weeks to 12 years old. We work on fostering a secure home-like environment that encourages children to become proactive and well-adjusted learners. Whenever you leave your child with us, please know that you are leaving them in reliable and caring hands. Smart Start Daycare in Wichita, Kansas began in our owner, Nicole McAdams’, home more than 12 years ago. In transforming her house into a daycare center, she has gained a lot of experience and knowledge which she uses to guide us today. Our company has since expanded to include a Pre-School program and Food Program to ensure the all-inclusive development of your children from early on.

I am licensed with KDHE, enrolled to accept DCF families and I provide nutritious meals and snacks reimbursed by a federally funded food program. I am CPR and First Aid certified with all the applicable training in place to be the best I can be while caring for your little ones. details: I am a licensed provider and will care for your children as if they were my own. I help them to learn through play and give them the tools to thrive.

Philosophy: It is our hope that your child will be enriched as a result of being part of our childcare home. All children enrolled are treated with love and respect. We feel children learn best in a natural learning environment. Consequently, your child will learn everyday by being part of an extended family. Patience, sharing, responsibility, compassion, communication and teamwork are the foundational building blocks that comprise the social stimulates your child will experience in our home. Our primary goal is to provide a safe and happy environment for each child. As a result, we provide loving care that focuses on each child as a unique and wonderful individual and in doing so, builds your child's self-esteem and respect for other's. Curriculum: Our main objective is to provide curriculum that will promote social, intellectual, emotional and most of all Spiritual growth in your child. Learning experiences appropriate for the age of your child are provided daily. We use a variety of curriculum centered on Signing Time and ABEKA Book. This is a sign language curriculum combined with a non-denominational Christian curriculum that provides each child with a Bible centered foundation of instruction.

I am here to help tend to the hearts of the little ones in my care. We will learn gross motor, fine motor, letter, shape, and number, recognition and so much more through hands on experiences. This home is here to be a loving and respectful environment for your child to grow up in. DCF payments will be excepted and we are also on the food program.
